handle,  but  decided  to  chose  Raven as some of my
friends  already called me "Rabe" (German for Raven).
I  got  the  name from a winter-vacation, where I set
free  a Raven captured in a fence. He got his freedom
afterwards, I got bloody hands and a new nickname. At
the end of my C64-time I was shortly a member of good
old  ×031Razor×  but  when  I switched from the C64 to the
Amiga  I  felt that some changes have to happen. That
was  the point when I renamed to ×031Abstract× and founded
×031NUANCE×  in  1991  with some friends. It took me quite
some   time   to   switch   from   C64-Pixeling   to
Amiga-Pixeling  with  all the colors and resolutions.
After  some time I set a rule for my scene- activity:
Born  on  the  Amiga  as  a  NUANCE-Guy.  I'll stay a
NUANCE-guy for the rest of my life. This also was the
point when I returned to my roots and renamed back to
Raven.  (Nickswitching rules...and causes confusion!)
;) At some certain point, when I started to freelance
with   some   game-companies,

I  realised  that  even the great Amiga can't give me
the power I need and so I switched to the PC. First I
tried  to  continue  my  pixelstyle, but soon changed
over  to a graphicstablet and Photoshop. Nowadays I'm
32  years  old,  live  with  my  girlfriend in a nice
appartment in the middle of Ulm/Germany and work as a
leading graphician for web-, gui- and print-design in
a  small  company  also  located  in Ulm. Sometimes a
quite stressy job that even eats the time that I want
to spend for the scene, but overall it's nice because
of  the  varieties  I  can  work at. Beneath that I'm
still  active in organizing NUANCE and doing graphics
and design (when time allows) for our productions. At
the  moment  we're  working  on a pc-production to be
released  at the Breakpoint this easter, a PC-Version
of our good old Chippack Trilobyte and some more nice
things.  
