B:  What  kind  of  role  does  Religion,  demons and
dragons   play   in   your   art?×

R:  I'm not religious in any way, either good or bad.
My religion, if you chose to call it that way, is the
human  mind, that should basically know what is right
or  wrong.  I  don't  believe  in any kind of god and
overall I like demons and dragon for the entertaining
qualities.  Also it can create a quite huge thrill to
combine  strong  or evil and weak parts in a picture,
means  for  example a beautiful woman and a dragon or
demon.
×008
B:  Any  other  motive,  objects, and perspective you
find   more   intresting   than   others?×
R: As mentioned before, the female body is one of the
most  beautiful  motives  to paint for me, as it is a
struggle for the own personal perfection. To find the
perfect  shape.  Beneath that, I like to paint nearly
everything  and  ×008I  also  like to see a picture grow,×
×008have  it's  own  life  and  result in Images I didn't×
×008intend.×

Overall  I also like closer views. Wide sceneries are
not  my type. I like straight motives that don't show
lots   of   objects   in   one   picture.

Also  I  like  to  use  different  techniques  for my
pictures. Most of my digital arts are painted using a
pencil before. And when it comes to traditional arts,
I like to draw with a lot of different techniques and
styles.  Up  to now I used pencil, pastel chalks, oil
pastel  chalks,  acrylic   paint,   airbrushing   and
charcoal.  I  even  started some weeks ago to go into
sculpturing   with   wood.
