any   yummy   n   tasty   anecdotes   to   share?×

R:  The  scene  gives  me  a  lot  of  nice things to
remember for my whole life.

One time, travelling home from a party (if I remember
right it was the ×031"Doomsday"-Party× in 1994) I told the
driver  of  the  other  car (×031Trasher/Sanity×) to drive
before me, because I didn't know the way. So we drove
the  long way home and after some time I asked myself
what  kind  of  crap  Trasher  is driving to. But who
cares. I just followed him,believing he knew the way.
Then we drove through small, crappy towns and finally
into  a small road. When suddenly the car in front of
me  stopped  and  a old man jumped out of the car and
attacked  the  car  I  drove  with  a umbrella in his
hands.
Well.  I  just  was losing ×031Trasher× on the highway and
followed a other car that looked alike. Maybe the old
man  thought  we  were  about to rob him or something
like  that.  Trasher laughed his ass off when hearing
the  story  afterwards. ;) 
                           Also nice was this one: We
were bored at the ×031Sun'n'Fun Conference II× during 1993
in Hellenthal. So we walked through the crappy little
town and entertained ourself with kickin on the poles
of  street  laterns. Once kicked, the lights went out
because  of  the  shock  for  around  1-2 Minutes. We
kicked  around 15 lamps while drinking some beers and
singing  and  imitating famous chiptunes. I was quite
drunk,  when  I kicked one of the poles and one of my
shoes  was flying over a fence into a small garden. I
climbed over the fence and was searching for my shoe.
It  was  fucking  dark and I couldn't see more than a
meter.  Then  I  saw  my sports shoe some metres away
because  of  his  neon  stripes.  Running there was a
mistake. A big splash and I entered the small pond in
the  middle  of  the garden. The lights went on and a
girl  shouted:  "Stand  still or I'll call the cops".
All   the   other   sceners   saved   their   asses.
Understandable.  Well.  I  had  to  explain why I was
sitting  in  the  pond in her garden. She laughed her
ass  off  and  brought me a towel. And it was quite a
nice  chick.  I  still  have her phone number and she
writes  a letter from time to time. friendship. Nice.
;)  These are just two of the things that happened to
me   during   scene-parties.   Enough?   ;)
